allLocations = inputJson[\"location\"]\n\n    if (!(allLocations instanceof List) || allLocations.isEmpty()) {\n        log.error(\"No valid 'location' array found in input JSON\")\n        session.transfer(flowFile, REL_FAILURE)\n        return\n    }\n\n    // Define batch size\n    def batchSize = 50\n    def total = allLocations.size()\n    def chunks = allLocations.collate(batchSize)\n\n    log.info(\"Splitting ${total} locations into ${chunks.size()} batches of ${batchSize}\")\n\n    // Create new FlowFiles for each batch\n    chunks.eachWithIndex { chunk, idx ->\n        def body = [\n            \"datetimerange-fromTime\": fromTime,\n            \"datetimerange-toTime\": toTime,\n            \"location\": chunk\n        ]\n\n        def jsonOut = JsonOutput.prettyPrint(JsonOutput.toJson(body))\n\n        def newFlowFile = session.create(flowFile)\n        newFlowFile = session.write(newFlowFile, { inputStream, outputStream ->\n            outputStream.write(jsonOut.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\n        } as StreamCallback)\n\n        newFlowFile = session.putAttribute(newFlowFile, \"chunk.index\", (idx + 1).toString())\n newFlowFile = session.putAttribute(newFlowFile, \"location.count\", chunk.size().toString())\n\n        session.transfer(newFlowFile, REL_SUCCESS)\n    }\n\n    // Remove the original (unsplit) flowfile\n    session.remove(flowFile)\n\n} catch (Exception e) {\n    log.error(\"Error splitting JSON: \" + e.message, e)\n    session.transfer(flowFile, REL_FAILURE)\n}",

H:mm\").withZone(ZoneId.of(\"UTC\"))\n\n// Wrap NiFi FlowFile handling\ndef flowFile = session.get()\nif (!flowFile) return\n\nflowFile = session.write(flowFile, { inputStream, outputStream ->\n    // start_time and end_time from FlowFile attributes\n    def startTime = flowFile.getAttribute(\"startTime\")?.toLong()\n    def endTime = flowFile.getAttribute(\"endTime\")?.toLong()\n\n    if (!startTime || !endTime) {\n        throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"FlowFile missing startTime or endTime attributes\")\n    }\n\n    def transformed = []\n\n    data.each { parent ->\n def entrySum = (stat.entryStats?.sum ?: 0) + (stat.exitStats?.sum ?: 0)\n            def compositeKey = \"${stat.locationid}_${hourFormatted}\"\n            def id = UUID.randomUUID().toString()  // Generate unique ID\n\n            transformed << [\n                id         : id,\n                primary_key: compositeKey,\n                locationid : stat.locationid,\n                hours      : hourFormatted,\n                entry_sum  : entrySum,\n                start_time : formatter.format(Instant.ofEpochMilli(startTime)),\n                end_time   : formatter.format(Instant.ofEpochMilli(endTime))\n            ]\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Write transformed JSON back to FlowFile\n    def outputJson = JsonOutput.prettyPrint(JsonOutput.toJson(transformed))\n    outputStream.write(outputJson.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\n\n} as StreamCallback)\n\nsession.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)",

java.time.ZonedDateTime\nimport java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter\nimport java.util.Date\n\nclass TransformCallback implements StreamCallback {\n    def fromTime\n    def toTime\n    def hasData = true  // <--- added flag\n\t\t\t\t   \n\n    TransformCallback(fromTime, toTime) {\n        this.fromTime = fromTime\n        this.toTime = toTime\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \n    }\n\n    @Override\n    void process(InputStream inputStream, OutputStream outputStream) throws IOException {\n        def parser = new JsonSlurper()\n        def parsed = parser.parse(inputStream)\n        // def now = ZonedDateTime.now().format(DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(\"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"))\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t   \n        // If response is empty array or null -> skip writing and mark flag\n        if (!parsed || (parsed instanceof List && parsed.isEmpty())) {\n            hasData = false\n            return\n        }\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  \n\n        def records = (parsed instanceof List) ? parsed : [parsed]\n        def transformed = []\n\n        records.each { rec ->\n            def entryExit = (rec.entry_exit instanceof List && rec.entry_exit) ? rec.entry_exit[0] : [:]\n            def cab = (rec.cab instanceof List && rec.cab) ? rec.cab[0] : [:]\n\n            def direction = entryExit.direction ?: \"unknown\"\n            def timestamp = entryExit.timestamp\n\n            def newRec = [:]\n            newRec[\"_id\"] = rec._id\n            newRec[\"direction\"] = direction\n            newRec[\"locationId\"] = entryExit.locationId\n            newRec[\"objectType\"] = entryExit.objectType\n            newRec[\"licensePlateNo\"] = rec._id\n            newRec[\"cab_type\"] = cab.cab_type\n            newRec[\"service_provider\"] = cab.service_provider\n            newRec[\"cab_sno\"] = cab.sno\n            newRec[\"cab_status\"] = cab.status\n            newRec[\"cab_updated_date\"] = cab.updated_date\n            // newRec[\"inserted_at\"] = now\n            // newRec[\"updated_at\"] = now\n\n            // Add start_time and end_time from FlowFile attributes\n            newRec[\"start_time\"] = fromTime\n            newRec[\"end_time\"] = toTime\n\n            // Add only one of entry_time or exit_time\n            if (direction == \"entry\" && timestamp) {\n                newRec[\"entry_time\"] = timestamp\n            } else if (direction == \"exit\" && timestamp) {\n                newRec[\"exit_time\"] = timestamp\n            }\n\n            transformed << newRec\n        }\n\n        // If no valid records\n        if (transformed.isEmpty()) {\n            hasData = false\n            return\n        }\n\n\t   \n        def jsonOut = JsonOutput.prettyPrint(JsonOutput.toJson(transformed))\n        outputStream.write(jsonOut.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\n    }\n}\n\n// --- Main NiFi Section ---\nflowFile = session.get()\nif (!flowFile) return\n\n// Read time range attributes from FlowFile (set in UpdateAttribute)\ndef fromTime = flowFile.getAttribute('datetimerange-fromTime')\ndef toTime = flowFile.getAttribute('datetimerange-toTime')\n\n// Inject them into the transformation\ndef transformCallback = new TransformCallback(fromTime, toTime)\nflowFile = session.write(flowFile, transformCallback)\n\n// If no data was written, remove FlowFile\nif (!transformCallback.hasData) {\n    log.info(\"No data found in JSON response  removing FlowFile.\")\n    session.remove(flowFile)\n    return\n}\n\n// Continue normally\nflowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile, 'mime.type', 'application/json')\nsession.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)",

groovy.json.JsonOutput\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit\n\n// === CONFIGURABLE WAIT TIME (in seconds) ===\ndef WAIT_SECONDS = 10\ndef CHUNK_SIZE = 15  // number of records per flow file\n\ndef flowFiles = []\ndef startTime = System.currentTimeMillis()\n\n// Collect all currently available flow files\nwhile (true) {\n    def ff = session.get()\n    if (!ff) break\n    flowFiles << ff\n}\n\n// If no flowfiles, exit\nif (flowFiles.isEmpty()) return\n\ntry {\n    // Wait for others to arrive (up to WAIT_SECONDS)\n    log.info(\"Waiting ${WAIT_SECONDS}s to collect all flow files for merging...\")\n    TimeUnit.SECONDS.sleep(WAIT_SECONDS)\n\n    // Try to pull any remaining flow files after wait\n    while (true) {\n        def ff = session.get()\n        if (!ff) break\n        flowFiles << ff\n    }\n\n    def idSet = new HashSet<String>()\n    def jsonSlurper = new JsonSlurper()\n\n    // Read all flow files and aggregate unique IDs\n    flowFiles.each { ff ->\n        def text = new StringBuilder()\n        session.read(ff, new InputStreamCallback() {\n            @Override\n            void process(InputStream inputStream) throws IOException {\n                text.append(new String(inputStream.bytes, StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\n            }\n        })\n        def arr = jsonSlurper.parseText(text.toString())\n        if (arr instanceof List) {\n            arr.each { idSet.add(it.toString()) }\n        } else {\n            log.warn(\"FlowFile ${ff.getAttribute('filename')} does not contain a JSON array\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Convert to list\n    def mergedList = idSet as List\n    def total = mergedList.size()\n    log.info(\"Merged ${flowFiles.size()} flow files  ${total} unique IDs\")\n\n    // === Split into multiple flow files of CHUNK_SIZE ===\n    int numChunks = (int) Math.ceil(total / (double) CHUNK_SIZE)\n\n    (0..<numChunks).each { i ->\n        def start = i * CHUNK_SIZE\n        def end = Math.min(start + CHUNK_SIZE, total)\n        def chunk = mergedList.subList(start, end)\n        def chunkJson = JsonOutput.toJson(chunk)\n\n        def chunkFlowFile = session.create()\n        chunkFlowFile = session.write(chunkFlowFile, new StreamCallback() {\n            @Override\n            void process(InputStream inputStream, OutputStream outputStream) throws IOException {\n                outputStream.write(chunkJson.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\n            }\n        })\n\n        chunkFlowFile = session.putAttribute(chunkFlowFile, \"record.count\", chunk.size().toString())\n        chunkFlowFile = session.putAttribute(chunkFlowFile, \"chunk.index\", (i + 1).toString())\n        chunkFlowFile = session.putAttribute(chunkFlowFile, \"filename\", \"merged_unique_ids_chunk_${i + 1}.json\")\n\n        session.transfer(chunkFlowFile, REL_SUCCESS)\n    }\n\n    // Remove original input flow files\n    flowFiles.each { session.remove(it) }\n\n} catch (Exception e) {\n    log.error(\"Error merging FlowFiles: ${e.message}\", e)\n    flowFiles.each { session.transfer(it,
